40|$|Geometrical optics can be {{regarded}} both as the short-wavelength approximation of the propagation of electromagnetic waves, and as the exact way in which propagate the <b>surfaces</b> <b>of</b> <b>discontinuity</b> <b>of</b> the classical electromagnetic field. In this work we translate this last idea to quantum mechanics (both relativistic and nonrelativistic). We find that the <b>surfaces</b> <b>of</b> <b>discontinuity</b> <b>of</b> the wave function propagate exactly following the classical trajectories determined by the Hamilton-Jacobi equation. As an example, we consider the lack of diffraction of abrupt wave fronts...|$|R
