40|$|In {{this paper}} we derive W^ 1,∞ and {{piecewise}} C^ 1,α estimates for solutions, and their t-derivatives, of divergence form parabolic systems with coefficients piecewise Hölder continuous in space variables x and smooth in t. This {{is an extension}} to parabolic systems of results of Li and Nirenberg on elliptic systems. These estimates depend on the shape and the size <b>of</b> the <b>surfaces</b> <b>of</b> <b>discontinuity</b> <b>of</b> the coefficients, but are independent of the distance between these surfaces. Comment: A new result is added which extends an L^p estimate of Campanato for strongly parabolic systems to rather weak parabolic systems, see Appendi...|$|R
